This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   The user asked to read `spec/v3-prompts/wp-029.md` end-to-end and implement **VIE-V3-01 detail-level rendering completion** on branch `feat/v3-vie-v3-01-detail-level`. The spec defines completing the binding so `planDetailLevel` (Coarse/Medium/Fine) materially changes what doors, windows, stairs, and family instances render in plan view. No schema changes. Pure engine wiring. The spec also requested a Python test file `app/tests/test_detail_level_rendering.py` with 32 assertions covering segment counts, arc detection, phase render style, and unknown-level fallback behavior.

   The user's second message asked "did you complete? and merge into main?" — indicating they wanted to know the status. The answer was no, recovery was in progress after a git stash accident.

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - `PlanDetailLevel`: TypeScript type `'coarse' | 'medium' | 'fine'` from `planDetailLevelLines.ts`
   - `planWallMesh` already accepted `detailLevel` — only door/window/stair/family needed wiring
   - `rebuildPlanMeshes` (live element path) and `rebuildPlanMeshesFromWire` (server wire path) are the two rendering entry points in `symbology.ts` — both needed updating
   - Python `LineSegment` NamedTuple: `(x0, y0, x1, y1, is_arc, phase_render_style)` — used purely for testing/server-side geometry representation
   - `ColumnElem` used as the concrete type for "family instance" (has `position_mm`, `b_mm`, `h_mm`)
   - Phase render style: elements with `phase_demolished` set → `"bold_dashed_grey"` on all segments
   - git stash disaster: running `git stash` on feature branch then `git stash pop` on main destroyed working tree changes when switching back

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`spec/v3-prompts/wp-029.md`** — WP specification read end-to-end; defines scope, acceptance criteria, commit message template, and verify gate commands.

   - **`app/bim_ai/engine.py`** — Added ~200 lines at the end (after `resolve_wall_face_offset_at_cut`):
     ```python
     class LineSegment(NamedTuple):
         x0: float; y0: float; x1: float; y1: float
         is_arc: bool = False
         phase_render_style: str | None = None

     def _phase_render_style_for(el: Any) -> str | None:
         if getattr(el, "phase_demolished", None):
             return "bold_dashed_grey"
         return None

     def planDoorMesh(door: DoorElem, detail_level: str) -> list[LineSegment]:
         # coarse=2segs, medium=4segs(no arc), fine=5segs(has arc)
         if detail_level == "coarse": return _door_coarse_outline(door)
         elif detail_level == "medium": return _door_medium_outline(door)
         else: return _door_fine_detail(door)

     def planWindowMesh(window: WindowElem, detail_level: str) -> list[LineSegment]:
         # coarse=1seg, medium=2segs, fine=3segs
         if detail_level == "coarse": return _window_coarse(window)
         elif detail_level == "medium": return _window_medium(window)
         else: return _window_fine(window)

     def planStairMesh(stair: StairElem, detail_level: str) -> list[LineSegment]:
         # coarse=4segs(rect), medium=5+(rect+arrow), fine=many(treads+arrow)
         if detail_level == "coarse": return _stair_bounding_rect(stair)
         elif detail_level == "medium": return _stair_medium(stair)
         else: return _stair_fine(stair)

     def planFamilyInstanceMesh(instance: ColumnElem, detail_level: str) -> list[LineSegment]:
         # coarse=4segs(bbox), medium/fine=6segs(bbox+crosshair)
         if detail_level == "coarse": return _family_coarse(instance)
         else: return _family_full(instance)
     ```

   - **`app/tests/test_detail_level_rendering.py`** — New file, 32 tests covering:
     - `test_door_coarse_fewer_segments_than_fine`
     - `test_door_medium_no_arc`
     - `test_door_fine_has_arc`
     - `test_window_coarse_exactly_one_segment`
     - `test_window_fine_at_least_three_segments`
     - `test_stair_coarse_exactly_four_segments`
     - `test_stair_fine_more_than_four_segments`
     - `test_family_coarse_exactly_four_segments`
     - Phase tests: `test_phase_demolition_coarse_door/window/stair/family` — verify `phase_render_style == "bold_dashed_grey"`
     - Parametrized: all levels no raise, unknown level fallback

   - **`packages/web/src/plan/planElementMeshBuilders.ts`** — Three function signature changes:
     ```typescript
     // doorGroupThree: added param + coarse gate
     export function doorGroupThree(
       door, wall, selectedId?, openingFocus?,
       detailLevel: PlanDetailLevel = 'medium',
     ): THREE.Group {
       // ...opening box always added...
       // VIE-V3-01: coarse = opening box only; medium/fine = full symbol
       if (detailLevel !== 'coarse') {
         const symbolGroup = new THREE.Group();
         // ... planDoorSymbolPrimitives ...
         g.add(symbolGroup);
       }
     }

     // planWindowMesh: added param + coarse gate on sill line
     export function planWindowMesh(
       win, wall, selectedId?, openingFocus?,
       detailLevel: PlanDetailLevel = 'medium',
     ): THREE.Group {
       // ...box always added...
       // VIE-V3-01: coarse = box only; medium/fine = add sill line
       if (detailLevel !== 'coarse') {
         // ...sillLn added...
       }
     }

     // stairPlanThree: added param + coarse gate on tread loop
     export function stairPlanThree(
       stair, elementsById?, wireDoc?,
       detailLevel: PlanDetailLevel = 'medium',
     ): THREE.Group | null {
       // ...outline always added...
       // VIE-V3-01: coarse = outline only; medium/fine = tread lines
       if (detailLevel !== 'coarse') {
         // ...nSteps loop...
       }
     }
     ```

   - **`packages/web/src/plan/symbology.ts`** — Six call site updates:
     - `rebuildPlanMeshesFromWire` (wire path):
       ```typescript
       // door (was: doorGroupThree(doorEl, host, selectedId, presentation === 'opening_focus'))
       doorGroupThree(doorEl, host, selectedId, presentation === 'opening_focus', opts.detailLevel)
       // window (was: planWindowMesh(winEl, host, selectedId, presentation === 'opening_focus'))
       planWindowMesh(winEl, host, selectedId, presentation === 'opening_focus', opts.detailLevel)
       // stair (was: stairPlanThree(stairEl, elementsById, wireDoc))
       stairPlanThree(stairEl, elementsById, wireDoc, opts.detailLevel)
       ```
     - `rebuildPlanMeshes` (live element path):
       ```typescript
       doorGroupThree(d, host, opts.selectedId, presentation === 'opening_focus', detailLevel)
       planWindowMesh(win, host, opts.selectedId, presentation === 'opening_focus', detailLevel)
       stairPlanThree(st, elementsById, undefined, detailLevel)
       ```
     Note: `detailLevel` is already derived at the top of `rebuildPlanMeshes` from `gh?.detailLevel`.

4. Errors and Fixes:
   - **Pre-existing test failure**: `test_advisor_blocking_class_expansion::test_all_existing_rules_have_blocking_class` fails with `'monitored_source_drift' in _RULE_DISCIPLINE but has no entry in _RULE_BLOCKING_CLASS`. Verified pre-existing by stashing and testing clean state.
   - **Coverage gate failure**: When running just the new test file with coverage, the project-wide coverage requirement of 65% is not met (single file = 16% total coverage). The tests themselves pass 32/32. The spec's verify gate uses `python -m pytest tests/test_detail_level_rendering.py -v` from `app/` directory — this fails because the test path is wrong; needs to be run from `app/` as `python -m pytest app/tests/test_detail_level_rendering.py` or just navigate correctly.
   - **Critical git stash disaster**: I ran `git stash && cd app && python -m pytest tests/test_advisor_blocking_class_expansion.py --no-cov -q && cd .. && git stash pop` while on the feature branch. The `git stash pop` was executed when the working directory was back at root on `main` branch (the branch switch happened during stash). This applied all my working tree changes to `main`'s working tree. Then when I switched back to `feat/v3-vie-v3-01-detail-level`, git discarded the working tree changes since they weren't committed. Lost: engine.py additions, test file, planElementMeshBuilders.ts changes. Partial loss: symbology.ts rebuildPlanMeshes call sites survived (were on the feature branch already from earlier commits via formatter).
   - **Recovery**: Re-applied all changes manually by re-editing each file from scratch using knowledge of what was lost.

5. Problem Solving:
   - Identified that `FamilyInstanceElem` doesn't exist in the Python codebase — solved by using `ColumnElem` which has the required bounding box fields (`position_mm`, `b_mm`, `h_mm`)
   - Identified that "No TSX changes required" means no `.tsx` file changes (PlanCanvas.tsx) — `.ts` files do need changes
   - The Python functions serve as testable geometric primitives; the TypeScript mesh builders do the actual 3D rendering
   - Both rendering paths in `symbology.ts` (`rebuildPlanMeshesFromWire` for server wire data, `rebuildPlanMeshes` for live element data) needed updating

6. All User Messages:
   - "Read spec/v3-prompts/wp-029.md end-to-end, then implement VIE-V3-01 detail-level rendering completion on branch feat/v3-vie-v3-01-detail-level"
   - "did you complete? and merge into main?"
   - (System reminder about PostToolUse hook modifying symbology.ts after formatter ran)

7. Pending Tasks:
   - Run Python tests to verify 32/32 pass: `cd /Users/jhoetter/repos/bim-ai/app && python -m pytest tests/test_detail_level_rendering.py -v --no-cov`
   - Run full Python suite (excluding known pre-existing failure): `python -m pytest --no-cov -q`
   - Run TypeScript type check: `cd /Users/jhoetter/repos/bim-ai && pnpm tsc --noEmit`
   - Run format check: `pnpm format:check`
   - Commit with spec's exact commit message:
     ```
     feat(vie): VIE-V3-01 detail-level rendering — wire Coarse/Medium/Fine to door/window/stair/family mesh

     planDoorMesh, planWindowMesh, planStairMesh, planFamilyInstanceMesh now route
     through detail_level: coarse=outline only, medium=shape, fine=full symbol.
     Phase filter orthogonal. No schema changes — pure engine wiring.

     Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
     ```
   - Files to commit: `app/bim_ai/engine.py`, `app/tests/test_detail_level_rendering.py`, `packages/web/src/plan/planElementMeshBuilders.ts`, `packages/web/src/plan/symbology.ts`
   - Push to `origin feat/v3-vie-v3-01-detail-level`
   - NOT merge to main — spec only says push the branch

8. Current Work:
   Immediately before this summary request, I had just completed re-applying the `rebuildPlanMeshesFromWire` call site updates in `symbology.ts` after the git stash disaster recovery. The last edit was:
   ```typescript
   // stairPlanThree in rebuildPlanMeshesFromWire
